---
import Container from "../layout/Container.astro";
import SectionLine from "../ui/SectionLine.astro";
---

<section class="relative mt-20 lg:mt-32">
  <SectionLine />

  <!-- Top: Two-column full-width layout (Figma: left dark panel + right image) -->
  <div class="w-full flex flex-col lg:flex-row min-h-105 lg:min-h-125">

    <!-- Left: Dark panel with label, title, button -->
    <div 
      class="lg:w-[40%] bg-black flex flex-col justify-end py-14 lg:py-20 px-8" 
      style="padding-left: max(2rem, calc((100vw - 1280px) / 2));"
    >
      <div class="max-w-md w-full">
        <p class="section-label text-white mb-0">
          <span class="text-brand">/05</span> ABOUT
        </p>
        <h2 class="section-title text-white mt-4 mb-10">About us</h2>
        <a href="#" class="flex items-stretch group cursor-pointer h-fit no-underline w-fit">
          <div class="bg-brand px-8 py-4 text-black font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-[16px] group-hover:bg-brand-hover transition-colors">
            More about us
          </div>
          <div class="bg-brand border-l border-black/10 px-4 flex items-center justify-center group-hover:bg-brand-hover transition-colors">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="black" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="group-hover:translate-x-1 transition-transform duration-300">
              <path d="M5 12h14"></path><path d="m12 5 7 7-7 7"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Right: Image filling full column -->
    <div class="lg:w-[60%] relative overflow-hidden min-h-70">
      <img
        src="/images/abouttv.webp"
        alt="About us"
        class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover transition-all duration-700"
      />
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Bottom: Dark 3-column content -->
  <div class="bg-feature-card">
    <Container class="py-20">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-12 lg:gap-20">
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-6 md:border-l md:border-white/10 md:pl-10">
          <p class="text-[15px] font-bold text-zinc-600 tracking-wider">/01</p>
          <div class="w-16 h-[1px] bg-brand/30"></div>
          <p class="section-subtitle text-zinc-100">
            HumbleBeeAI Academy exists because <span class="italic text-white">"knowing"</span> is not the same as <span class="italic text-white">"being able to deliver."</span> Resumes and short interviews often miss what matters: consistency, coachability, and real output quality.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="flex flex-col gap-6 md:border-l md:border-white/10 md:pl-10">
          <p class="text-[15px] font-bold text-zinc-600 tracking-wider">/02</p>
          <div class="w-16 h-[1px] bg-brand/30"></div>
          <p class="section-subtitle text-zinc-400">
            So we built a full-time, mentor-reviewed environment that trains and measures those traits through real work. Students follow deadlines, reviews, documentation standards, and iterative improvement - then graduate with evidence of capability, not just learning completion.
            <br /><br />
            The outcome is simple: proof-of-skill you can demonstrate, plus an evaluation record shaped through <span class="text-white underline decoration-zinc-600 underline-offset-8">RISE</span>.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="flex flex-col gap-6 md:border-l md:border-white/10 md:pl-10">
          <p class="text-[15px] font-bold text-zinc-600 tracking-wider">/03</p>
          <div class="w-16 h-[1px] bg-brand/30"></div>
          <p class="section-subtitle text-zinc-400">
            And we take a clear position on what modern engineering requires: AI is the new horsepower. The people who thrive won't be those who merely "use tools," but those who can ride AI with control and responsibility - understanding data, training choices, ethics, and real-world application.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </div>

  <SectionLine />
</section>
